{
  "title": "Viary Privacy Policy",
  "effectiveDate": "October 25, 2025",
  "body": "Effective Date: October 25, 2025\nLast Updated: October 25, 2025\n\n1. Overview\n\n  This Privacy Policy explains how Viary (\"we\", \"us\", the \"App\") collects, uses, stores, shares, and deletes personal information, and informs you of your rights. We follow global privacy principles (data minimization, purpose limitation, storage limitation, integrity/confidentiality, transparency).\n\n2. Information We Collect and How\n\n  We collect only the minimum information necessary to provide the service.\n\n  Account Information (optional)\n   - Items: Email, profile name/photo, user ID (UID), social login provider info (e.g., Google)\n   - Method: When you sign up/sign in via Firebase Authentication\n\n  Subscription & Payments\n   - Items: Active entitlements, purchase status, restore history (we do NOT collect card details)\n   - Method: Via RevenueCat SDK and the Apple App Store/Google Play billing systems\n\n  Support/Contact\n   - Items: Category, subject/body, app version, OS/device info, UID\n   - Method: When you contact us via email or in-app inquiry\n\n3. How We Use Information\n\n  To provide recording/memo/visualization features, manage accounts (authentication/login/enforcement), handle subscriptions and purchases, provide support, and improve the service (statistics, debugging, security, and new features).\n\n4. Retention\n\n  We process/retain data only for lawful periods or as consented.\n   - Account: Deleted without undue delay upon account deletion or end of legal retention\n   - Subscription/Payment records: Retained per applicable e-commerce/tax laws (typically 5 years)\n   - Consumer complaints/dispute records: Retained per applicable laws (typically 3 years)\n   - Principle: Voice files are stored on your device under your control. They are not stored on our servers and cannot be recovered after you uninstall the App.\n   - Exception (AI features): If you choose AI analysis/summary, voice data is sent ephemerally to Google Gemini API and deleted immediately after processing.\n\n5. Deletion Procedures & Methods\n\n  We delete data without undue delay when the retention period ends or the purpose is fulfilled. Electronic files are irreversibly deleted; paper records are shredded/incinerated.\n\n6. Processors (Service Providers)\n\n  - Google LLC (Firebase Authentication): Sign-up/sign-in authentication\n  - RevenueCat, Inc.: Subscription and entitlement management\n  - Apple Inc., Google LLC: App marketplace billing\n  - Google LLC (Gemini Developer API): AI processing when you opt in\n\n7. International Data Transfers\n\n  Your data may be transferred to/processed in countries such as the United States where our service providers are located. We use appropriate safeguards (e.g., Standard Contractual Clauses) to protect your data.\n\n8. Your Rights and How to Exercise Them\n\n  Depending on your jurisdiction, you may request access, correction, deletion, restriction, portability, or object to processing. You may also withdraw consent where processing is based on consent. Use the in-app account deletion feature or contact: jhaislab@gmail.com. We will respond without undue delay and inform you if any legal grounds require refusal.\n\n9. Security Measures\n\n  We implement organizational/technical/physical safeguards, including least-privilege access, access control, TLS in transit, encryption of key data, log retention and tamper protection, anti-malware and security programs, and physical access controls.\n\n10. Data Protection Contact\n\n  Data Protection Contact: Lee Jeong-hoon\n  Email: jhaislab@gmail.com\n\n11. Remedies\n\n  You can contact local supervisory authorities in your region for privacy inquiries or complaints.\n\n12. Changes\n\n  We will notify you of material changes at least 7 days in advance in the App (30 days for significant changes to your rights).\n\n13. Contact\n\n  Email: jhaislab@gmail.com (we may need to verify your identity).\n\n14. Cookies & Behavioral Data\n\n  We do not collect behavioral advertising data. As a mobile app, we do not use browser cookies; only minimal local storage is used for functionality.\n\n15. Incident Notification\n\n  In case of a personal data breach, we will notify in accordance with applicable laws and take required actions."
}
